A composite literal whose `{` opens a line closes on its own line too. gofmt
never does this: go/printer decides the `}` break solely from whether the SOURCE
already put `}` on a later line (nodes.go:294), so `{\n\ta: 1}` stays welded shut.

Block-form braces and field-breaking are independent, and breakWideLiterals keys
on the BRACE line. The Import / Export item's `{` opens its own (short) line, so
its fields stay packed even though their line overflows — only the closing brace
moves. The Analytics and Admin items are written fully inline, and at width 80
their brace lines (96 and 90 columns) are over budget, so breakWideLiterals
breaks their fields one per line — the ordinary wide-literal remedy, reached now
that an unsplittable wide line earlier in the slice no longer starves later
literals of their turn.

-- input.gsx --
package ui

var appShellNavSections = []appShellNavSection{
	{
		label: "TOOLS",
		items: []appShellNavItem{
			{
				label: "Import / Export", page: ImportExportPage{}, pathMatch: "/import-export/", nonVendor: true, vendorVisible: func(u *db.UserInfo) bool { return u.HasGrantPrefix("", "import") }, },
			{label: "Analytics", page: DashboardLanding{}, pathMatch: "/dashboard/", nonVendor: true},
			{label: "Admin", page: AdminDashboardPage{}, pathMatch: "/admin/", adminOnly: true},
		},
	},
}
-- fmt.golden --
package ui

var appShellNavSections = []appShellNavSection{
	{
		label: "TOOLS",
		items: []appShellNavItem{
			{
				label: "Import / Export", page: ImportExportPage{}, pathMatch: "/import-export/", nonVendor: true, vendorVisible: func(u *db.UserInfo) bool { return u.HasGrantPrefix("", "import") },
			},
			{
				label:     "Analytics",
				page:      DashboardLanding{},
				pathMatch: "/dashboard/",
				nonVendor: true,
			},
			{
				label:     "Admin",
				page:      AdminDashboardPage{},
				pathMatch: "/admin/",
				adminOnly: true,
			},
		},
	},
}
